| # | Finding | OWASP Category | Severity | Effort |
|---|---------|---------------|----------|--------|
| 1 | No input validation | A03 – Injection | 🔴 High | Low |
| 2 | No security headers | A05 – Misconfiguration | 🔴 High | Low |
| 3 | No rate limiting | A04 – Insecure Design | 🔴 High | Low |
| 4 | No CORS policy | A01 – Broken Access Control | 🟠 Medium | Low |
| 5 | PII exposed unauthenticated | A01 / A02 | 🟠 Medium | Medium |
| 6 | No auth framework | A07 – Auth Failures | 🟠 Medium | High |
| 7 | Server fingerprinting | A05 – Misconfiguration | 🟠 Medium | Low |
| 8 | No error handling | A05 – Misconfiguration | 🟡 Low | Low |
| 9 | Hardcoded config | A05 – Misconfiguration | 🟡 Low | Low |
| 10 | No audit logging | A09 – Logging Failures | 🟡 Low | Low |

